==Facts== *The AAGPBL, which drew as many as one million people during one season, was founded in 1943 by the [[Chicago Cubs]]' owner, [[Philip K. Wrigley]], to keep fan interest alive during [[World War II]]. The league folded in 1954, but there is now a permanent display at the [[Baseball Hall of Fame and Museum]] at [[Cooperstown, New York]] since November 5, {{by|1988}} that honors those who were part of this unforgettable experience.
*In [[1992 in film|1992]], [[filmmaker]] [[Penny Marshall]] premiered her film ''[[A League of Their Own]]'', which was a [[fiction]]alized account of activities in the AAGPBL. Starring [[Geena Davis]], [[Tom Hanks]], [[Madonna (entertainer)|Madonna]], [[Lori Petty]] and [[Rosie O'Donnell]], this film brought a rejuvenated interest to the women's baseball.
